"""Database migrations using Alembic.

This package contains database migration scripts managed by Alembic.

## Usage

### Create a new migration

```bash
alembic revision -m "description of changes"
```

### Run migrations (upgrade to latest)

```bash
alembic upgrade head
```

### Run migrations (upgrade specific version)

```bash
alembic upgrade <revision>
```

### Downgrade migrations

```bash
alembic downgrade -1  # Downgrade one revision
alembic downgrade <revision>  # Downgrade to specific revision
```

### View current revision

```bash
alembic current
```

### View migration history

```bash
alembic history
```

## Environment Variables

- `DATABASE_URL` - Direct PostgreSQL connection string (preferred for migrations)
- `SUPABASE_URL` and `SUPABASE_KEY` - Used as fallback if DATABASE_URL not set

For Supabase, use the direct connection string from your Supabase dashboard:
Settings > Database > Connection string > URI (direct connection)
